ion therapy</article-title><source>Europace</source><year>2007</year><volume>10</volume><fpage>959</fpage><lpage>998</lpage></element-citation></ref><ref id="R14"><label>14</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Perez de Isla</surname><given-names>L</given-names></name><name><surname>Florit</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><name><surname>Garcia-Fernandez</surname><given-names>MA</given-names></name><name><surname>Evangelista</surname><given-names>A</given-names></name><name><surname>Zamorano </surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><article-title>Prevalence of echocardiographically detected ventricular asynchrony in patients with left ventricular systolic dysfunction.</article-title><source>J Am Soc Echocardiogr</source><year>2005</year><volume>18</volume><fpage>850</fpage><lpage>859</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">16084338</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="R15"><label>15</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Penicka</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name><name><surname>Bartunek</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><name><surname>De Bruyne</surname><given-names>B</given-names></name><name><surname>Vanderheyden</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name><name><surname>Goethals</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name><name><surname>De Zutter</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name><etal>et al.</etal><article-title>Improvement of left ventricular function after cardiac resynchronization therapy is predicted by tissue Doppler imaging echocardiography.</article-title><source>Circulation</source><year>2004</year><volume>109</volume><fpage>978</fpage><lpage>983</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">14769701</pub-id></element-citation></ref></ref-list></back></article>